                        <!-- SETTINGS OVERVIEW -->
                        <Border Background="#f3f4f6" BorderBrush="#d1d5db" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="8" Padding="15" Margin="0,0,0,12">
                            <StackPanel>
                                <TextBlock Text="⚙️ Settings — Making the App Yours" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="17" Foreground="#1f2937" Margin="0,0,0,8"/>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12.5" Foreground="#374151" LineHeight="21">
The Settings window is divided into five tabs, each dedicated to a specific area. Here is what each tab does:
                                </TextBlock>

                                <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Foreground="#0369a1" Margin="0,10,0,3">❶ Daily Prayer</TextBlock>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,5" LineHeight="20">
Set your location (search by city name or enter coordinates directly). Choose your calculation method from over 20 options including MWL, ISNA, Makkah, Egypt, and many country-specific methods. Pick your madhab (Shafi or Hanafi) for Asr time calculation, set the time format (12h or 24h), adjust the Hijri date offset if your local moon sighting differs, and configure Suhur/Iftar offsets. You can also set fixed congregation (Jamaat) times for each prayer, which then display in the taskbar timer and trigger congregation popup alarms.
                                </TextBlock>

                                <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Foreground="#166534" Margin="0,10,0,3">❷ Tracker</TextBlock>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,5" LineHeight="20">
Enable or disable the daily tracker. Configure the Deed popup (how long after Jamaat it appears) and the Daily Summary popup (scheduled time). Set up automatic data backups on your preferred schedule (daily/weekly/monthly) and choose where to save them. The Auto-Track Ramadan option automatically enables tracker focus during Ramadan.
                                </TextBlock>

                                <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Foreground="#92400e" Margin="0,10,0,3">❸ Notifications</TextBlock>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,5" LineHeight="20">
Granular control over every sound and alert in the app. Enable or disable Adhan sounds per prayer (Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, Isha), adjust the global Adhan volume, and choose from 14 built-in Adhan tracks by famous reciters (Makkah, Mishary Alafasi, Nasser Alqatami, etc.) or use your own custom MP3/WAV file. There is also a separate Fajr-specific Adhan path for those who use a different track for Fajr. Pre-Adhan reminders send a toast notification before each prayer at your chosen offset. Congregation popups alert you before each Jamaat time. Prayer notification sounds (start/end voice alerts) can be enabled in your preferred language (English, Bangla, or Arabic). Tahajjud alarms help you wake for the last third of the night with a custom sound.
                                </TextBlock>

                                <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Foreground="#4f46e5" Margin="0,10,0,3">❹ Layout &amp; Theme</TextBlock>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,5" LineHeight="20">
Toggle the Floating Overlay, the legacy DeskBand, the Integrated Taskbar Timer (Windows 11 style), and the Enhanced Taskbar Timer (TrafficMonitor-style with color-coded status dot and adjustable position). Set the interface language to English or Bangla (বাংলা). Customize the gradient start and end colors, plus primary and secondary accent colors. Show or hide the prayer times grid in the hero card, enable notifications, configure auto-start with Windows (with optional silent start), and toggle external API usage for Hijri data.
                                </TextBlock>

                                <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Foreground="#5b21b6" Margin="0,10,0,3">❺ Support &amp; Contact</TextBlock>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,5" LineHeight="20">
Check for updates, view the current version, find official resources (website, Telegram channel), explore the developer's other projects, support the developer via SupportKori, and access links to the developer's portfolio and package registries.
                                </TextBlock>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </Border>

                        <!-- TASKBAR FEATURES -->
                        <Border Background="#fdf2f8" BorderBrush="#fbcfe8" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="8" Padding="15" Margin="0,0,0,12">
                            <StackPanel>
                                <TextBlock Text="🖥️ Taskbar Integration — Prayer Times at a Glance" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="17" Foreground="#9d174d" Margin="0,0,0,8"/>
                                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12.5" Foreground="#374151" LineHeight="21">
One of the app's standout features is how it integrates with your Windows taskbar. You have three options, which you can enable independently from Settings &gt; Layout &amp; Theme:
                                </TextBlock>
                                <BulletDecorator Margin="0,6,0,2">
                                    <BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                        <TextBlock Text="🪟" FontSize="12"/>
                                    </BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                    <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,0"><Bold>Floating Overlay:</Bold> A small semi-transparent panel that hovers on your desktop edge, showing the current prayer and countdown. It pops up vertically on hover for more details.</TextBlock>
                                </BulletDecorator>
                                <BulletDecorator Margin="0,3,0,2">
                                    <BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                        <TextBlock Text="📌" FontSize="12"/>
                                    </BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                    <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,0"><Bold>Legacy DeskBand:</Bold> A classic Windows taskbar toolbar extension, great for Windows 10 users or those using ExplorerPatcher on Windows 11.</TextBlock>
                                </BulletDecorator>
                                <BulletDecorator Margin="0,3,0,2">
                                    <BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                        <TextBlock Text="🔲" FontSize="12"/>
                                    </BulletDecorator.Bullet>
                                    <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="#374151" Margin="10,0,0,0"><Bold>Enhanced Taskbar Timer:</Bold> The most modern option. Sits directly on your taskbar with no visible window border. Shows the current prayer, a live countdown, and the next prayer's name in a single compact line. A color-coded dot tells you the status at a glance — green for active prayer, yellow when less than 10 minutes remain, red during prohibited times, and gray for upcoming prayers. Choose from four positions: Left of Tray, Right of Tray, Center, or Left Near Start.</TextBlock>
                                </BulletDecorator>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </Border>

